Dependency=Census Division RECS: # Description: The size of an attached garage.
# Source: Constructed using U.S. EIA 2020 Residential Energy Consumption Survey (RECS) microdata.
# Assumption: Only Single-Family Detached homes are assigned a probability for attached garage.
# Assumption: No garage for ambient (i.e., pier & beam) foundation type.

# Assumption: Due to modeling constraints restricting that garage cannot be larger or deeper than livable space: Single-family detached units that are 0-1499 square feet can only have a maximum of a 1 car garage.
# Assumption: Single-family detached units that are 0-1499 square feet and 3+ stories cannot have a garage.
# Assumption: The geometry stories distributions are all the same except for 0-1499 square feet and 3 stories.
# Assumption: Single-family detached units that are 1500-2499 square feet can not have a 3 car garage.
# Assumption: Single-family detached units that are 2500-3999 square feet and a heated basement can not have a 3 car garage. Due to low sample sizes, 1. Crawl, basements, and slab are lumped.
# Assumption: 2. Story levels are lumped together.
# Assumption: 2. Census Division RECS is grouped into Census Region.
# Assumption: 2. Vintage ACS is progressively grouped into: pre-1960, 1960-1999, and 2000+.
